        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 12:15AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1215 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Pearsonia, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Bigheart...                       Pearsonia...
Dewey...                          Bartlesville Municipal Airport...
Ochelata...                       Tallant...
Pawhuska...                       Sunset Lake...
Osage Hills State Park...         Bartlesville...
Nelagoney...                      Okesa...
Ramona...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for
northeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
